messages.content:
Here’s the slide deck with speaker notes added for each slide. The notes provide talking points and examples you can use while presenting.

```json
{
  "title": "The Future of Remote Work",
  "slides": [
    {
      "title": "Slide 1",
      "bullet_points": ["Remote work growth driven by tech, expectations, and global events"],
      "speaker_notes": "Explain how advancements like video conferencing, cloud collaboration, and the pandemic accelerated remote work. Mention statistics: 70% of companies plan to keep remote options post‑COVID."
    },
    {
      "title": "Slide 2",
      "bullet_points": ["Shift to hybrid models and re‑imagined office spaces"],
      "speaker_notes": "Describe hybrid models (e.g., 3‑days in‑office, 2‑days remote). Talk about office redesigns focused on collaboration zones rather than desks."
    },
    {
      "title": "Slide 3",
      "bullet_points": ["Investment in asynchronous communication tools"],
      "speaker_notes": "Highlight tools like Slack, Loom, and Notion that support async work. Share a case study where async reduced meeting time by 30%."
    },
    {
      "title": "Slide 4",
      "bullet_points": ["Challenges: culture, equity, productivity"],
      "speaker_notes": "Discuss difficulty maintaining company culture virtually, ensuring equity across time zones, and measuring productivity without micromanagement. Offer mitigation strategies."
    },
    {
      "title": "Slide 5",
      "bullet_points": ["Benefits: flexibility, talent pool expansion, cost savings"],
      "speaker_notes": "Emphasize employee satisfaction, access to global talent, and reduced overhead (e.g., $11k saved per employee per year on office space)."
    },
    {
      "title": "Slide 6",
      "bullet_points": ["Best practices for managing distributed teams"],
      "speaker_notes": "Provide practical tips: clear OKRs, regular check‑ins, virtual coffee breaks, and fostering psychological safety."
    },
    {
      "title": "Slide 7",
      "bullet_points": ["Future predictions for the next decade"],
      "speaker_notes": "Project trends: AI‑driven remote collaboration, fully virtual headquarters, and increased emphasis on employee well‑being. End with a Q&A invitation."
    }
  ]
}
```
